        "protagonistas":"Adam",
        "sinopsis":"As Omega Point prepares to launch an all-out assault on The Reestablishment soldiers stationed in Sector 45, Adam's focus couldn't be further from the upcoming battle. He's reeling from his breakup with Juliette, scared for his best friend's life, and as concerned as ever for his brother James's safety. And just as Adam begins to wonder if this life is really for him, the alarms sound. It's time for war.<br>On the battlefield, it seems like the odds are in their favor—but taking down Warner, Adam's newly discovered half brother, won't be that easy. The Reestablishment can't tolerate a rebellion, and they'll do anything to crush the resistance... including killing everyone Adam has ever cared about.",
        "cita":"“Okay then. Let’s go get our girl back.”<br> “My girl,” I correct him. <br>“She’s my girl.” Kenji snorts as we head in the direction of the compounds. <br> “Right. Minus the part where she’s not actually your girl. Not anymore.”<br> “Shut up.”<br> “Uh-huh.” <br>“Whatever.”<br><br>“All I can think is how horrible and beautiful it is, that our eyes blur the truth when we can't bear to see it.”",
