        "protagonistas":"Kenji",
        "sinopsis":"The explosive revelations in Defy Me have left readers reeling and desperate for answers. This fourth and final novella in the series will bring readers back to the world of the Shatter Me before the final novel installment hits shelves in winter 2020.",
        "cita":"“With her, it’s different. I never even realized just how much I was missing until we really got to know each other. She lets me talk. She doesn’t rush me. She doesn’t tell me to calm down or feed me bullshit lines or tell me everything will be fine. When I’m trying to get things off my chest she doesn’t make the conversation about her or her own problems. She understands. I can tell. She doesn’t have to say a word. I can look into her eyes and know she gets it. She gives a shit about me in a way no one else ever has.”<br><br>“You were looking at her like you were in love with her!”<br>“Jesus Christ, woman, I look at you like I'm in love with you!”<br><br>“Please, love. Just ignore it.” <br>“What if something’s wrong?”<br> “Nothing is wrong,” he says. “It’s just Kenji.” <br>“Kenji?” I hear some kind of shuffle, and my heart picks up. J always comes through. She always comes through. “How do you know it’s Kenji?”<br>“Call it a wild guess,” Warner says. I ring the doorbell again. “Coming!” J. Finally. “She’s not coming,” Warner shouts. “Go away.”<br>“I’m not going anywhere,” I shout back. “I want to talk to Juliette. Ella. Jella. Jello. Whatever.”<br>“Ella, love, please—let me kill him.” I hear J laugh, which is sweet, actually, because it’s clear she thinks Warner’s joking. Me, on the other hand—I’m pretty sure he’s not.”<br><br>“Here, in the dark, with my memories. Sometimes I feel so alone in this world I can’t even breathe.”<br><br>“Peor: no se como salir de aqui. ¿Donde esta el boton de expulsion para escapar de conversaciones con mujeres aterradoras y hermosas?”",
